On Fri, 3 Dec 2004, Mark Hineline wrote:

> Suppose I were to drive a bus from San Diego to Maine and then leave it
> garaged in Maine.
>
> Where would I register it?

Sounds like the garage is where it (and you) live for purposes of
registration.

Most states have no problem with sending the registration renewals to an
out-of-state address.  They just want the money.

You might even want to register it in a "state of convenience" like the
full-time RV folks.  Here's some info:

http://www.motorhomemagazine.com/forums/index.cfm/fuseaction/thread/tid/14611872/gotomsg/14612214.cfm


George
